      title="Frontend Developer"
      subtitle="2023 to Present at Lucid Motors, Newark, California"
    >
    <div class="pl-3">
      <ul class="list-disc">
      <li> Developing front end website architecture.</li>
      <li> Building comprehensive, interactive software applications.</li>
      <li> Collaborating with back-end developers and web designers to improve usability.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    </TimeLineElement>

    <TimeLineElement
      title="Postdoctoral Researcher"
      subtitle="2018 to 2021 at University of Rochester, Rochester, New York"
    >
    <div class="pl-3">
      <ul class="list-disc">
      <li> Authored over 20 peer-reviewed publications with a total citation count 490 and mentored 5 students.</li>
      <li> Programmed computer-based tests with Python and Matlab for a range of individuals.</li>
      <li> Applied machine learning techniques to multimodal neuroimaging (functional and structural MRI, functional connectivity, diffusion MRI) and psychophysiology data using Python, R, and Matlab.</li>
      <li> Developed an innovative computational approach to identify specific brain markers, which can serve as a potential target for developing effective cognitive training.</li>
      <li> Utilized a novel sliding window approach for identifying task-independent ECG shapelets which successfully predicted cognitive and neural gains after training.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    </TimeLineElement>
  </div>

